# Project Constitution: MOV to MP4 Converter

## Code Quality
- Write clean, readable, and maintainable code
- Follow PEP 8 style guide for Python
- Use type hints for function signatures
- Add docstrings for all functions and classes
- Keep functions small and focused on single responsibilities

## Testing Standards
- Write unit tests for core functionality
- Test error handling and edge cases
- Aim for high code coverage on critical paths
- Include integration tests for the conversion pipeline

## User Experience
- Provide clear and helpful error messages
- Show progress feedback during conversions
- Make the CLI intuitive with sensible defaults
- Include help documentation and usage examples
- Handle interruptions gracefully (Ctrl+C)

## Performance
- Support batch processing efficiently
- Use multiprocessing for concurrent conversions when possible
- Optimize memory usage for large files
- Provide estimated time remaining for long conversions

## Dependencies
- Minimize external dependencies
- Use well-maintained and popular libraries
- Document all dependencies clearly
- Ensure cross-platform compatibility (Windows, macOS, Linux)
